      "text": "Last edit about 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n132\nNeeds Review\n132\n26 Then it can be seen why Plato could not solve the problem as to how the unitary eidos pluralized itself in/as particulars at different space-time loce. The answer is: it doesn't. Plato was on the right track in regarding the particulars as only semireal. If he had understood that spatiotem porality is illusory he would have realized that this pluralization of an eidos is only seeming, due to our use of space, time + causation as",
